    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">King Ferdinand I to Miklós Oláh (Graz, 16 December 1552)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">He has been informed that Oláh has arrived to Bruck an
                            der Mur. He orders him to come straight to the court with his immediate
                            accompaniment, and he should leave his servants whom he can do without
                            for a few days in Bruck. He should not take umbrage that he is not
                            receiving him in airy Ebersdorf, but he will be ten days late because he
                            has made a detour to Leoben. Lestár Feledi and György Rakovszky are
                            rumoured to be with him; he should bring them, too.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Ferdinandus etc. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">Intelleximus Devotionem Tuam in oppidum nostrum
                        <placeName>Buckam</placeName><note xml:id="note.1">Bruck an der Mur.</note>
                    salvam et incolumem apprendisse idque nobis pro nostra etiam <choice>
                        <orig><gap extent="1" reason="illegible" unit="word"/></orig>
                        <supplied><corr>eadem</corr></supplied>
                    </choice> clementia nobis <choice>
                        <orig><gap extent="1" reason="illegible" unit="word"/></orig>
                        <supplied><corr>magis</corr></supplied>
                    </choice> atque gratum accedit. Quare eidem nunc clementer committimus, ut <del
                        corresp="scriba">minori</del><add corresp="scriba" type="corr">minima</add>
                    qua poterit familia cras se recta huc ad aulam nostram regiam conferat, et <del
                        corresp="scriba">reliquam familiae suae partem</del> reliquos servitores
                        <del corresp="scriba">quibus</del> suos, <del corresp="scriba">quibus carere
                        potest</del> quos non semper <del corresp="scriba">ad</del> necesse est
                    Devotioni Tuae ad manum esse istic <placeName>Bruckae</placeName> per aliquot
                    adhuc dies relinquas, neque id gravetur attente, quod nos etiam licet in arce
                    nostra <placeName>Eberstorff</placeName><note xml:id="note.2">Ebersdorf.</note>
                    satis multum <del corresp="scriba">aurae</del> salubris aurae ceperimus te et
                    non recta huc profecti sumus, sed <del corresp="scriba">prius antea per diem
                        dies</del><add corresp="scriba" type="corr">ex itinere</add> in oppidum
                    nostrum <placeName>Leoben</placeName> divertimus, et ibi decem dies moram
                    habuerimus. Factum est eo etc.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.3">Datum <placeName>Gratz</placeName> 16. Decembris 1552.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.4">Postscripta cum intelligamus etiam cum Devotione Tua esse <gap
                        extent="1" reason="illegible" unit="word"/> fidelem nobis dilectum
                        <persName>Eustachium a Veledy</persName><note xml:id="note.3">Lestár
                        Feledi.</note> et <persName>Georgium Rakowsky</persName>.<note
                        xml:id="note.4">György Rakovszky.</note> Ideo volumus quod ipsos quoque <gap
                        extent="1" reason="illegible" unit="word"/> adducat.</p>
            </div>
            <div style="handwritten" type="verso" xml:id="d.2">
                <head>Probably on the outer side:</head>
                <p xml:id="p.5">Cancellario Hungarico.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
